full_description:

Speaker:: Mark Smith

Track: PyCon: Programming & Software Engineering
On every computer I've had for the past 20 years, I've created a folder called "stupid python tricks".
It's where I put code that should never see the light of day.
Code that abuses advanced features like decorators, metaclasses, and dynamic typing to do terrible things.

Code I'm going to teach you.


Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022.
https://2022.pycon.de
More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/N9RV8L
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
